# Code ownership → who GitHub auto-requests for review.
#
# No default/wildcard entry on purpose: files *not* listed below (new
# condition files, their tests, docs) need no code-owner review — anyone can
# approve those. Only the paths listed here — the harness, scoring, models,
# and the Condition contract itself, which contributors' A2–A9 conditions
# build on top of and shouldn't change as part of adding a condition — route
# to @advaitsangle specifically.
#
# To actually enforce this, turn on branch protection for `main`:
#   - Require a pull request before merging
#   - Require review from Code Owners
#   - Require status checks to pass (select the CI job)
#   - Include administrators (optional, but keeps you honest)

# --- Frozen core: the harness and scoring seam ---
/vulnbench/harness.py               @advaitsangle
/vulnbench/checkpoint.py            @advaitsangle
/vulnbench/suite.py                 @advaitsangle
/vulnbench/report.py                @advaitsangle
/vulnbench/cli.py                   @advaitsangle
/vulnbench/schema.py                @advaitsangle
/vulnbench/scoring/                 @advaitsangle
/vulnbench/models/                  @advaitsangle

# --- The Condition contract itself ---
# base.py defines run(target, ctx) -> ConditionResult; __init__.py is the
# REGISTRY. New conditions add a *new file* + one registry line — changes to
# these two files are the seam and get owner review.
/vulnbench/conditions/base.py       @advaitsangle
/vulnbench/conditions/__init__.py   @advaitsangle

# --- Project + CI config ---
/pyproject.toml                     @advaitsangle
/.github/                           @advaitsangle
